  <brief_title>Safety and Effectiveness Study of the Solysafe Septal Occluder in Patients With Atrial Septum Defect and Patent Foramen Ovale</brief_title>
  <official_title>Prospective Multicenter Clinical Study to Evaluate the Safety and Effectiveness of an Intracardiac Septal Closure Device in Patients With Atrial Septum Defect (ASD) and Patent Foramen Ovale (PFO)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Carag AG</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Carag AG</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a prospective multicenter clinical study to evaluate the safety and effectiveness of
      an intracardiac septal closure device in patients with atrial septum defect (ASD) and patent
      foramen ovale (PFO).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Completed</overall_status>
  <phase>N/A</phase>
